Sentencas: Bilayer electrolytes composed of a gadolinium-doped CeO2 (GDC) layer (similar to 6 mu m thickness) and an yttria-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) layer with various thicknesses (similar to 330 nm, similar to 440 nm, and similar to 1 mu m) were deposited by a pulsed laser deposition (PLD) technique for thin film solid oxide fuel cells (TFSOFCs).
Titulo: High power density thin film SOFCs with YSZ/GDC bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The bilayer electrolytes were prepared between a NiO-YSZ (60:40 wt.% with 7.5 wt.% carbon) anode and La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (50:50 wt.%) composite cathode for anode-supported single cells.
Titulo: High power density thin film SOFCs with YSZ/GDC bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: Significantly enhanced maximum power density was achieved, i.e., a maximum power density of 188, 430, and 587 mW cm(-2) was measured in a bilayer electrolyte single cell with similar to 330 nm thin YSZ at 650, 700, and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: High power density thin film SOFCs with YSZ/GDC bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell with the bilayer electrolyte (YSZ similar to 330 nm) doubles the overall power output at 750 degrees C compared to that achieved in the GDC single layer cell.
Titulo: High power density thin film SOFCs with YSZ/GDC bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: This signifies that the YSZ thin film serves as a blocking layer for preventing electrical current leakage in the GDC layer and also provides chemical, mechanical, and structural integrity in the cell, which leads to the overall enhanced performance.
Titulo: High power density thin film SOFCs with YSZ/GDC bilayer electrolyte
